HB 580 Original 2026 Regular Session Mandie Landry
Abstract: Prohibits sellers or agents from conducting real estate activity in which fees or
conditions are hidden from a potential buyer or lessee.
Present law provides for definitions.
Proposed law adds definitions for "real estate activity" and "seller".
Present law provides what no person shall do regarding real estate service agreements.
Proposed law adds that no person shall conduct real estate activity, including a public
advertisement or listing for sale or lease, that deceives, misleads, or hides a fee or condition
from a prospective buyer or lessee. A fee or condition disclosed only after a prospective
buyer or lessee pays an application fee shall be considered hidden.
(Amends R.S. 51:1429(A); Adds R.S. 51:1429(B)(3))
